id: pm-5909
title: "CI gap: plugin/package markdown pushed to main runs no functional workflow"
description: "ci.yml:7-12 push paths-ignore includes '**/*.md' (plus redundant CHANGELOG.md/CONTRIBUTING.md entries already covered by the glob), while docs.yml:4-23 push/PR paths cover only docs/**, .agents/skills/**, root *.md, CHANGELOG/CONTRIBUTING, ISSUE_TEMPLATE. plugins/**/*.md (slash commands, skills, subagent prompts — functional plugin assets validated by scripts/smoke-claude-plugin.mjs) and packages/**/README.md are ignored by CI on push AND not matched by Docs, so a direct push to main touching only plugin markdown runs no gate except CodeQL. PRs are unaffected (ci.yml pull_request has no paths filter). Fix options: add 'plugins/**' (or '!plugins/**/*.md' style carve-out) to ci.yml paths-ignore exceptions, or extend docs.yml paths with plugins/** and packages/**/*.md so the docs-skills gate + smoke runs. Severity low (workflow discipline is PR-based) but it is the one push-path hole; everything else in .github/workflows is healthy: all actions SHA-pinned, least-privilege permissions blocks, concurrency groups, pnpm+tsbuildinfo+lancedb caches, release.yml Sentry reliability gate intact (:113-121) with auto-release pre-flight token guard (auto-release.yml:114-118), last 15 runs green incl today's Auto Release -> Release chain."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 3
